@startuml SignalCaptureAI_Georouting_Workflow
title SignalCaptureAI - Data Capture Workflow (Risk Highlighted)
skinparam style strictuml
skinparam wrapWidth 200

legend top right
  **Risk Levels (Transactions & Actor Swimlanes)**
  |<#White> White Box | Internal / Trusted Execution (Low Risk) |
  |<#E6F2FF> <color:black>Light Blue Lane</color> | Internal Trusted System Boundary |
  |<#Orange> Orange Box | PII Processing (Medium Risk) |
  |<#FFE6CC> <color:black>Light Orange Lane</color>| Edge Gateway Transit (Medium Risk) |
  |<#Red> <color:white>Red Box</color> | External Data Ingress-Egress (High Risk) |
  |<#FFCCCC> <color:black>Light Red Lane</color>| Untrusted External Actors (High Risk) |
endlegend

|#FFCCCC|Sales Rep|
start
:Access SignalCaptureAI Platform;

|#FFE6CC|Cloudflare (Geo-Barrier)|
:Detect Initial Request Geolocation;

|#E6F2FF|Azure Application (Docker)|
:Serve Web Application & Capture Geo-Headers;

|#FFCCCC|Sales Rep|
:Login via WorkOS SSO; <<#Orange>>

|#E6F2FF|Azure Application (Docker)|
:Cache Geolocation in Secure Session Token (JWT);

|#FFCCCC|Sales Rep|
:Select Event in App;
:Capture Business Card (Photo) \n& Record Voice Note; <<#Red>>

|#E6F2FF|Azure Application (Docker)|
:Receive Request & Extract Cached Geolocation;

if (Strict Local Data Residency Required?) then (No - Default to EU)

    |#LightBlue|Azure EU Backend (Primary Privacy-Hub)|
    :Process OCR & Transcribe Voice (Whisper) in EU; <<#Orange>>
    note right
        This includes the US, UK, Canada, and EU.
        US laws (CCPA) do not mandate data localization.
        Processing US data in the EU is legal 
        and adheres to the highest privacy standard (GDPR).
    end note
    :Store extracted PII in EU Tenant SQL DB \n(Encrypted via Keyfactor PKI); <<#Orange>>
    :AI cross-references transcript 
    with Product Docs;
    :Generate localized follow-up draft;

else (Yes - e.g., Strict Enterprise or China/India)

    |#LightGreen|Azure Localized Backend (Regional Spoke)|
    :Process OCR & Transcribe Voice (Whisper) locally; <<#Orange>>
    note right
        Specific sovereign requirements 
        (e.g., US Gov ITAR, specific enterprise contracts, 
        or strict localization laws in other countries).
    end note
    :Store extracted PII in Local Tenant SQL DB \n(Encrypted via Keyfactor PKI); <<#Orange>>
    :AI cross-references transcript 
    with Product Docs;
    :Generate localized follow-up draft;

endif

|#FFCCCC|Sales Rep|
:Human-in-the-loop: \nReview & Approve Draft Message;
:Dispatch Message (Email / WhatsApp); <<#Red>>

|#E6F2FF|Global Admin Dashboard|
:Aggregate Meta-Metrics;
note right
  Provides a "single pane of glass"
  visibility across multiple regions,
  while underlying data remains
  strictly isolated in its home region 
  to adhere to data compliance.
end note

|#E6F2FF|Global Admin Dashboard|
if (Data Subject Request?) then (Query/Delete)
    :Trigger Compliance Deletion/Query; <<#Orange>>
    :Target specific region's DB\nto execute request; <<#Orange>>
endif

stop
@enduml
